John CAVANAUGH, Appellant, v. Charles J. LONG, Appellee. No. 15530. United States Court of Appeals Ninth Circuit. Feb. 24, 1958. Grubic, Drendel & Bradley, William O. Bradley, Reno, Nev., for appellant. Perry W. Morton, Asst. Atty. Gen., Elizabeth Dudley, Atty., Dept, of Justice, Washington, D. C., Franklin P. R. Rit-tenhouse, U. S. Atty., Las Vegas, Nev., for appellee.

Before HEALY, LEMMON, and BARNES, Circuit Judges

PER CURIAM.

The judgment below is affirmed for the reasons given in the opinion and order of the trial judge on the motion to dismiss, Cavanaugh v. McKenzie, D.C., 159 F.Supp. 555.
